Method Detail

exists

boolean exists(java.lang.String ticket)
               throws DaoException
Returns true if there is a ticket with the specified code. Such parameter should be compared with the attribute Ticket.getTicket(). If there's is no ticket with the given code, returns false. If any exception is thrown by the underlying implementation, wrapped it in a DaoException.

Throws:
DaoException

load

<T extends Ticket> T load(java.lang.String ticket,
                          Relationship... fetch)
                      throws EntityNotFoundException,
                             DaoException
Retrieves the ticket identified by the attribute code, as returned by Ticket.getTicket(). If no ticket can be found, throws EntityNotFoundException. If any exception is thrown by the underlying implementation, wrapped it in a DaoException.

Throws:
DaoException
EntityNotFoundException

search

java.util.List<? extends Ticket> search(TicketQuery query)
Searches tickets given the query, ordering results by date descending. If no entity can be found, returns an empty list. If any exception is thrown by the underlying implementation, it should be wrapped by a DaoException.
